latestIgtvVideos.caption:
One of the things @priscillapresley shared with her late husband, Elvis, was a love of dressing up. When the couple decided to get married in 1967, Presley had a unique bridal dilemma: how to buy a wedding dress without being recognized and tipping off the paparazzi. 

“This was a well kept secret because we wanted it to be our wedding with our friends and not to be loaded with paparazzi,” she says. She ended up going to bridal boutiques dressed in sunglasses and accompanied by the musician and friend Charlie Hodge in order to stay anonymous. Head to the link in our bio for all the details on the iconic wedding and Priscilla's #LifeInLooks.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Floral Fridays
latestIgtvVideos.caption: For Vogue Wedding’s new series, Floral Fridays, wedding experts are sharing their floral expertise with us. For our first episode, Alexandra Griffin from @almakitchenco shares how she creates their gourmet botanical shortbreads with organic ingredients. For each box sold, a portion of the proceeds funds the planting of one tree.

latestPosts.caption: Reflecting on the wedding weekend, newlyweds @Jayda.Hawkinsss and @JaylinnHawkins share they don’t have a single regret. In their words, “We honestly couldn’t have prayed for it to go any smoother, and I think it perfectly reflected the peace and happiness and just pure joy that comes with knowing you found the right person.” Head to the link in bio to go inside the couple's wedding in Hawaii. latestPosts.caption:
When choosing her wedding day attire, @jayda.hawkinsss wanted to wear something minimal to complement the grandeur of her venue's backdrop. “With the wedding being both outside and in Hawaii, I also knew I didn’t want a big heavy dress,” she says. “Still, I wanted some drama.” 

The bride decided on a two-piece set by @septnewyork, complete with a custom-made long-line corset and a pleated chiffon skirt. @sarahseven also helped her create a dramatic moment with a cathedral-length veil lined with the same lace as the corset. To accessorize, she borrowed Hawaiian jewelry from her grandmother, including a plumeria necklace with matching earrings, a ring, and a bangle. See more photos of the couple's wedding in Hawaii at the link in bio. Photos: @sav.and.cam

latestPosts.caption:
When New England Patriots player @jaylinnhawkins first saw @jayda.hawkinsss while attending UC Berkeley, he knew she was the one. “I’m not trying to sound corny, but it was kind of like love at first sight,” shares Jaylinn. The two student-athletes started their relationship just as friends, since they were both dating other people. After graduation, Jayden moved to Los Angeles and Jaylin to Atlanta, but the two were able to reconnect when Jayda visited Atlanta for a friend's birthday. “We’ve talked every day since,” says Jaylinn. “When something’s meant to be, it will always find its way back to you.”

Jaylin and Jayda wed at Kualoa Ranch on Oahu, in March 2025. Since the bride's maternal family is from Hawaii, creating an authentic love letter to the island and their guests was the goal. “It meant everything to us that our guests didn’t just attend a wedding, but truly felt the spirit of the islands we love so much,” says Jayda, who worked with Laura Armendariz of @fawnevents to craft the celebration. See inside the couple's dreamy wedding in Oahu at the link in bio. Photos: @sav.and.cam

latestPosts.caption:
When @OliviaCulpo began planning her baby shower, she knew that there was only one place it could be: Rhode Island. The New England state is where she spent her childhood, where she married @christianmccaffrey, and where she became the person she is today. 

On May 4, she held a Parisian-inspired affair at Castle Hill Inn in Newport, planned by @LisaVorce and with creative direction by @LucioAndreozzi. Tap the link in bio to take an exclusive look inside Culpo’s “Bébé McCaffrey” baby shower. Video: @evanpaterakis

The 2025 #MetGala was filled with unlimited bridal inspiration. From @DianaRoss’s sweeping white gown, featuring an 18-foot train to Sir @LewisHamilton’s custom Grace Wales Bonner suit, tap the link in bio to go inside the fashion’s biggest night.

@lauraharrier stunned at the 2025 #MetGala, wearing a design by @zacposen for @gap. Their stylish presentation honored the theme “Superfine: Tailoring Black Style,” and is the perfect suit for brides who want a more tailored look without skipping out on the drama of a ball gown. Tap the link in bio for a closer look.

As we await to see what this year will bring, head to the link in bio to revisit our favorite bridal-worthy looks from fashion's biggest night out and see everything you need to know about this year's theme. Video: @gettyimages

@namraiva and Grid Soonthornpusit first met at a garden party in 2014, so it made perfect sense that their wedding 10 years later would be a floral-filled celebration. “That celebration felt both intimate and natural, and we knew we wanted to capture that same relaxed, carefree mood for our special day,” says the bride.

The Thai couple chose the Sri Panwa Hotel in Phuket to host the final event of their three-part wedding. On the day, the tropical hotel garden was accented with arrangements of green and white blooms in preparation for the ceremony. Tap the link in bio to see more photos from the couple's dreamy Thailand garden wedding. Photos: @nawaphon_present
